column5: Well, as per usual....... Skeeter-0 Daniel (my son )-1 Tracker 1+1  of course, as expected, i didnt catch anything !!! but, in my defence I did get the first hit..... but , never got it in.  heres Daniel's catch of the day a 24" 4.5" LB sheep head    and trackers first cat    his second fish, he released it before i even got the camera out. i just think he didnt want anyone to see his sheep head, but daniel is my witness. LOL  all in all we had a great day!

Was a great day - and I have the sunburned face this morning to prove it.  We did see 1 big kittie caught that was probably in the 8 lb. range , and a bunch of the small cats similar to the one I caught.  Sheephead? - what sheephead?
My first ever catch was a 7lb sheephead down at the fishermans pier in Hamilton, boy was I happy! Now I try not to bring it up haha.
7 lb sheep?  My first ever catch was a 7lb sheephead down at the fishermans pier in Hamilton, boy was I happy! Now I try not to bring it up haha.  its in black & white now---LOL
Hey Tracker !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! Why dont you tell all the good people here on the board about the line you found while we were there?????????????  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~  ~~~~  ~~~
